result.name: Yu Chuan Riben Izakaya Restaurant

reviews.text: Nice little Japanese izakaya. Plenty of food choices. We had the beef sukiyaki, ox tongue skewer and grilled mackerel which all tasted great. Expect price between $150-200 per head for dinner.
Unexpected fresh and worth eating Sushi. Sashimi Rice is good too and they serve warm fresh rice instead of overnight refrigerated rice.  Fried rice is great too. Highly recommended!

The ramen has surprised me with its high quality of ingredients including the egg and the pork. The seared pork tastes and smelled very meaty and together with the fat, it's so satisfying. I did not have the chance to order the most popular sushi but the ones I had are within expectations. Worth coming again!

Oh, the service was not exceptional, some staff were kind of intriguing too much.

U can use gulu app for taking ticket for waiting remotely. We had 5 people but have been waited for 1 more hours from C006 to C007. You can see the small table went so fast in the picture. Food are Normal so it doesn't worth the waiting.
Good good good
